5️⃣ Create Service Interface

Go to:

src/main/java/com/example

Create file:

CalculatorService.java

Code:

package com.example;

import javax.jws.WebMethod;
import javax.jws.WebService;

@WebService
public interface CalculatorService {

 @WebMethod
 int add(int num1, int num2);

 @WebMethod
 int subtract(int num1, int num2);
}
6️⃣ Implement the Service

Create file:

CalculatorServiceImpl.java

Code:

package com.example;

import javax.jws.WebService;

@WebService(endpointInterface = "com.example.CalculatorService")

public class CalculatorServiceImpl implements CalculatorService {

 public int add(int num1, int num2) {
  return num1 + num2;
 }

 public int subtract(int num1, int num2) {
  return num1 - num2;
 }
}
7️⃣ Create Server Class

Create file:

Server.java

Code:

package com.example;

import org.apache.cxf.jaxws.JaxWsServerFactoryBean;

public class Server {

 public static void main(String[] args) {

  JaxWsServerFactoryBean factory = new JaxWsServerFactoryBean();

  factory.setServiceClass(CalculatorService.class);
  factory.setAddress("http://localhost:8080/CalculatorService");
  factory.setServiceBean(new CalculatorServiceImpl());

  factory.create();

  System.out.println("SOAP Service Started at http://localhost:8080/CalculatorService");
 }
}
8️⃣ Build the Project

Run:

mvn clean install
9️⃣ Run the SOAP Server

Run:

mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="com.example.Server"

Output:

SOAP Service Started at http://localhost:8080/CalculatorService
🔟 Open WSDL in Browser

Open:

http://localhost:8080/CalculatorService?wsdl

You will see WSDL XML file describing the SOAP service. 

